<li>Class capacity and utilisation</li>
<li>Marketing campaign effectiveness</li>
</ul>

<h3>11. Lead and Trial Management</h3>

<p>Converting enquiries to enrolled students requires systematic follow-up. Lead management features include:</p>

<ul>
<li>Lead capture forms for website integration</li>
<li>Trial class scheduling and tracking</li>
<li>Automated follow-up sequences</li>
<li>Lead source tracking for marketing attribution</li>
<li>Conversion funnel reporting</li>
</ul>

<h3>12. Integration Capabilities</h3>

<p>No software operates in isolation. Integration capabilities extend functionality through connections with:</p>

<ul>
<li>Website and landing pages</li>
<li>Email marketing platforms (Mailchimp, etc.)</li>
<li>Accounting software (QuickBooks, Xero)</li>
<li>Calendar applications (Google Calendar, iCal)</li>
<li>Zapier and automation platforms</li>
<li>Social media platforms</li>
</ul>

<h2>Implementation and Onboarding</h2>

<p>Successful software implementation requires planning beyond simply signing up and logging in. A structured approach minimises disruption and maximises adoption.</p>

<h3>Pre-Implementation Planning</h3>

<ul>
<li>Audit current processes and identify pain points</li>
<li>Clean and organise existing student data for import</li>
<li>Document current pricing structures and membership types</li>
<li>Map belt curricula and progression requirements</li>
<li>Identify staff who will require training</li>
</ul>

<h3>Data Migration</h3>

<p>Migrating from existing systems—whether spreadsheets, another platform, or paper records—requires careful attention. Most platforms support importing:</p>

<ul>
<li>Student profiles and contact information</li>
<li>Membership and billing data</li>
<li>Attendance history (where available)</li>
<li>Belt rank and progression data</li>
</ul>

<strong>Allow 2-4 weeks for data migration and verification</strong> before going live with billing.

<h3>Staff Training</h3>

<p>Different staff roles require different training focus:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Front desk:</strong> Check-in, payments, basic member management</li>
<li><strong>Instructors:</strong> Attendance, progression notes, mobile app usage</li>
<li><strong>Owners/managers:</strong> Reporting, billing configuration, system administration</li>
</ul>

<h3>Realistic Timeline</h3>

<p>A typical implementation timeline spans <strong>4-8 weeks</strong>:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Weeks 1-2:</strong> Configuration, data import, testing</li>
<li><strong>Weeks 3-4:</strong> Staff training, parallel operation</li>
<li><strong>Weeks 5-6:</strong> Soft launch with new features</li>
<li><strong>Weeks 7-8:</strong> Full deployment, old system retirement</li>
</ul>

